reviewText: One of my very favorite Veidt movies, in a good quality format.  The older silent version, presumably much closer to the original play, is a curiosity but worth watching to better appreciate the 1930's version.
This DVD copy is poorly made. You can not hear the dialogue! Too bad, because this is a wonderful movie. U-tube have clearer copies.
